        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 12:01AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1200 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Crane, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
King Mountain and Midkiff.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
